The Issue: A company is struggling with "Shadow IT" (employees using unapproved apps).

The Solution: An audit mapping internal risks to the CIA Triad (Confidentiality, Integrity, Availability).

CIA-Triad-Audit.md

Scenario: Conducted a gap analysis for a mock firm.

Confidentiality: Identified that payroll data was accessible to the general HR group. Remedy: Restricted access to "Need-to-Know" only.

Integrity: Discovered that financial spreadsheets lacked version control. Remedy: Implemented "Digital Signatures" to track changes.

Availability: Found the server room lacked a backup power source. Remedy: Proposed a UPS (Uninterruptible Power Supply) installation.
